Explanation:

For even states in a finite symmetric well, matching the interior wavefunction ($A cos(k x)$) with the exterior wavefunction ($C sinh(kappa(b-x))$) and their derivatives at boundary $x=a$ yields the transcendental equation $k tan(k a) = kappa coth(kappa(b-a))$.
